When generating ResponseWrapper and RequestWrapper annotation, need to give the default value. 

for example:
@ResponseWrapper(targetNamespace = "http://demo.iona.com/", className = "com.iona.demo.SayHiResponse", localName = "sayHiResponse")
@RequestWrapper(targetNamespace = "http://demo.iona.com/", className = "com.iona.demo.SayHi", localName = "sayHi").
The reason:
jaxb type builder will generate type class such as com.iona.demo.SayHi.
But java2wsdl tool is looking for 'com.iona.demo.jaxws.SayHi' by default if we do not design 'className' in the RequestWrapper ann.

If we change the jaxb type builder to generate type class as 'com.iona.demo.jaxws.SayHi'. But the wsdl2java tool will generate jaxb type classes again in the default package 'com.iona.demo.SayHi'.

The only fix for this is define the correct value in the annotation.

