Having a long discussion with Tod today, I'd like to summerize the whole thing, the problems:

How does one would use the current API if we don't change:

--------------------8<--------------------
TableViewer v = new TableViewer(parent,SWT.BORDER|SWT.FULL_SELECTION);

TableColumn column = new TableColumn(v.getTable(),SWT.NONE);
ViewerColumn vColumn = v.getViewerColumn(0);
vColumn.setEditingSupport(new MyEditingSupport()); // NEW API

v.setLabelProvider(new MyLabelProvider()); // OLD API
v.setContentProvider(new MyContentProvider());
v.setInput(input);
--------------------8<--------------------

This works prefectly in conjunction with patch in bug #164839 the order when what is called shouldn't be a problem but we have programming style break in between. A much more natural way if we would provide the a streamlined API like this:

--------------------8<--------------------
TableViewer v = new TableViewer(parent,SWT.BORDER);

TableViewerColumn column = new TableViewerColumn(tableViewer,SWT.NONE);
column.setEditingSupport(new MyEditingSupportA()); // NEW API

v.setLabelProvider(new MyLabelProvider()); // OLD API
v.setContentProvider(new MyContentProvider());
v.setInput(input);
--------------------8<--------------------

It's not because this is 2 lines shorter. Usage of JFace feels much more natural than the first style and we don't expose any more API than we do already!

