If the package declaration is not the first line of a file (either because a comment is the first line or you are using the default package), then after folding an anonymous inner type, content assist breaks the editor window. Steps to reproduce:

Start with a simple class that has an anonymous inner class defined:

/** Comment is the first line here */

public class Class {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        new Runnable() {
            public void run() {}
        };

    }

}

Collapse the runnable:

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        new Runnable() {..

    }

}

Use content assist to define a new String:

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        new Runnable() {..

        new Str<ctrl-space>
    }

This leaves you with:

/** */

        new Runnable() {..

        new Str
    }

}

Upgrading to M3 half fixed the problem. (I also see the problem in 3.2 btw). Use the same initial class:

/** Comment is the first line here */
public class Class {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new Runnable() {
            public void run() {}
        };
    }
}

Follow the same instructions as before, but this time when you use content assist to complete the new String, save the file before adding the semi-colon (save the file with compiler error). This will have the same affect.

